___NOTES___

# OpenAI Ads Pixel: GTM Community Template

A Google Tag Manager Community Template for the OpenAI Ads Measurement Pixel
(`oaiq`).

**Created by:** Utku Gülden. https://www.linkedin.com/in/utku-gulden/
**Brand:** utkugulden
**License:** Apache 2.0

This is a community-maintained template. It is not affiliated with, endorsed,
or sponsored by OpenAI or Google.

## What it does

- Loads the OpenAI pixel SDK from `https://bzrcdn.openai.com/sdk/oaiq.min.js`
- Initializes the pixel with your Pixel ID (idempotent across multiple tag fires)
- Sends standard OpenAI events (page_viewed, order_created, lead_created and
  others) or custom events with your own names
- Maps fields to the official data shapes: `contents`, `customer_action`,
  `plan_enrollment`, `custom`
- Supports a single product, a pre-built multi-product `contents[]` array from
  a GTM variable, or no contents at all
- Forwards an `event_id` when set, and `custom_event_name` for custom events,
  both inside `eventOptions`
- Allows arbitrary extra fields via Additional Properties (key-value rows
  merged into eventProps after standard fields)

## References

- Pixel docs: https://developers.openai.com/ads/measurement-pixel
- Supported events: https://developers.openai.com/ads/supported-events

## Standard event names

| Event name              | Data shape         |
|-------------------------|--------------------|
| page_viewed             | contents           |
| contents_viewed         | contents           |
| items_added             | contents           |
| checkout_started        | contents           |
| order_created           | contents           |
| lead_created            | customer_action    |
| registration_completed  | customer_action    |
| appointment_scheduled   | customer_action    |
| subscription_created    | plan_enrollment    |
| trial_started           | plan_enrollment    |
| custom                  | custom             |

## Important behaviors

- `custom_event_name` and `event_id` are sent in **eventOptions**, never in
  `eventProps`. The template enforces this regardless of where users put them
  in the UI.
- `amount` and `quantity` are coerced to integers. `amount` must be in the
  currency's lowest denomination (e.g. cents for USD).
- When `amount` is set without `currency`, the template drops `amount` to keep
  the payload valid.
- Custom event names are validated: 1–64 characters, `[a-z0-9_-]`, and may not
  reuse a standard event name.
- The SDK and the pixel are initialized at most once per page (per pixel ID),
  even if multiple tags fire.
